         I don't know about all pets... but at least the spec pet DOES summon the max level every time.  Focused spec pet max level is 48.  I summoned a level 48 pet without fail.  So, that part is working just fine.  Just that the max level pet is hitting for 4 points less than it should.  So I have level 48 pets that hit for 67 without fail.</P><P>Everything that Rich is doing with the pets is awsome.  There is only one last big change that I think would make them about as raid friendly as they can be.  Pets need to be hit by group buffs and heals and the like.  The resists help a lot.  The aggro changes help a lot.  The new UI helps a lot because now the group can see your pet's health easily.  But, how long would most people last in a heavy AoE situation like ToV with no buffs (even if they had good resists)?  Not real long.  Or they'd be a mana sponge for the healer.  And I don't want to bug everyone for single buffs on my pet.  I know healers that don't even like HEALING pets.</P><P>Once that is done, I think pets will be fixed about as much as they can be.  They will still suffer against AE dispel type mobs but I don't really see how that can be fixed.  It'll just have to be one of the disadvantages.</P><P><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26159">Reegor</A> Mortees<BR>scaled Warlock<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
